name: Central San Francisco Urban Dream
description:
3 BR/2 BA Victorian flat beautifully restored with all the charming details, the comfort of modern amenities plus a beautiful garden to hang out in. One block to public transportation, walking distance to many great restaurants, shops and parks.

The space
3 BR/2 BA Victorian flat beautifully restored with all the charming details, the comfort of modern amenities plus a beautiful garden to hang out in. We are in the Lower Haight neighborhood (not Hayes Valley). Muni train 2 blocks away, several buses less than 1 block away. Walking distance to Haight Ashbury, NOPA, Hayes Valley and Castro restaurants, bars, shops and Golden Gate Park. We're close to the geographic center of San Francisco so you can get to the best neighborhoods easily from here.
There's loads of space for you and your family or friends. Come back to a comfortable, homey place after your day exploring the city. We are both travelers and explorers and have lots of info and maps of the r
neighborhood_overview:
Nearby market: Right out the front door, right at the corner. At the next corner (Haight and Scott) organic market on the right, regular corner store on the left

Big Grocery: Safeway at Market and Church

Cafe/coffee: For Haight street character: Cafe International (Haight and Fillmore); For a decent place to go with your laptop: Bean There (Steiner and Waller); For the Frenchie feel: Le Cafe du Soleil (Fillmore and Waller). Slightly further but very cute for breakfast/brunch: Cafe Flore (Market and Noe). If you are a coffee connoisseur - The Mill (Divisadero and Fulton)

Drinks: Famous for its beer on tap: Toronado (Haight between Steiner and Fillmore; get a sausage at Rosamunde next door while you are there); Funky: The Noc Noc (a few doors towards Steiner, next to Toronado); Trendy, fancy cocktails: Maven (Haight and Steiner). Several good bars at Divisadero between Fell and Fulton too (Madrone, MiniBar, the bar at NOPA, Fly Bar).
host_about: I am American of Indian decent and I live here with my husband who is Guatemalan and French and our dog (of unknown decent), Leela.  I've been in the bay area for 12 years so will have lots of travel ideas for you.  We love our home and would love to share it with a few good travelers.

name: Sunny 4-Bedroom Family Home Central SF Location
description:
Enjoy the best of urban village living in our light, spacious, 4-bedroom, 2 & 1/2 bath home in the heart of Bernal Heights, only two blocks from the restaurants, shops and galleries of Cortland Street. It's a short walk to the amazing Mission for food and drink and Bernal Hill for hiking and amazing views. Our home comfortably accommodates a family, or a larger group. Easy street parking with no residential parking permit required. Close to transit (BART, MUNI) and major freeways (101 and 280).

The space
This beautiful 4-bedroom, 2 1/2 bath home is nestled in the hip 'urban village' of Bernal Heights in San Francisco. The house is beautifully remodeled, with an open kitchen with granite countertops, brand new appliances, and hardwood floors. The master bedroom is spacious and has a queen-sized bed. The second bedroom is smaller, with a full-size bed (sleeps 2) and a desk. The third bedroom is perfect for a child with a twin loft bed, desk, and bookcase. The four
neighborhood_overview: Bernal Heights is a chic urban village full of restaurants, shops, and galleries. Spend your days wandering the cafes and shops of Cortland Street, or exploring the numerious gardens and parks the neighborhood has to offer. Definitely do not miss the view from the top of Bernal Hill  -- it offers unparalelled views of the city of San Francisco and San Francisco Bay. It's also one of the only places you can see both the Golden Gate Bridge and the Bay Bridge from one spot!
host_about: We are a tight-knit family of four with two wonderful, school-aged girls. This is our San Francisco home where, when we are traveling for business or personal reasons, we love having people from all over the world stay and enjoy our home, our neighborhood and our city!

name: Great Family Home, Quiet Street, Close to GG Park
description:
We love our home and hope you will, too. It's light, super clean (all AirBNB cleaning requirements...and then some), pretty modern, and very comfortable. We've got all the amenities, including a backyard, and can sleep 4 - 6. We live in a great neighborhood that has easy access to parks, shops and restaurants on Clement and Haight Street.

The space
Enjoy our beautiful home in the Inner Richmond neighborhood of San Francisco, just a few short blocks from Golden Gate Park, near University of San Francisco.

Our home was built in 1936, styled after Rousseau, a well-known architect, famous for his inner light-well/courtyard. Our house has a central atrium that spreads light through the main parts of the house. It has a great layout, with plenty of room to spread out. We love our home and think you will too.

Needless to say, we're taking all the Covid-19 precautions to make you and us feel safe. We follow AirbnbÃ¢â¬â¢s five-step enhanced cleaning p
neighborhood_overview: We are in a great SF neighborhood. We are on a quiet street and our home is close to major parks, walking distance to Clement St.
host_about:
I'm a native San Francisco and we have raised our family here with great joy. We love it! We are avid about the  outdoors, all the great restaurants, food trucks and farmer's markets (happy to share our favorite local spots) and going on our own version of walking tours all over the city, exploring the diverse neighborhoods that make SF so fabulous.

We too love to travel and like staying in homes vs. hotels so we thought we would share ours. We hope you love it as much as we do.

Our home is in the heart of The Mission district, the trendiest neighborhood in San Francisco. We are 1 block from Valencia street, which offers a vibrant nightlife as it is lined with fabulous restaurants, cafes and bars. There are also many fascinating unique shops selling everything from retro polaroid cameras to pirate supplies to vintage clothes and whimsical toys.

We are two blocks from Mission street and the small Mexican and South American businesses and family run restaurants. Nearby alleys feature he famous Mission murals.

name: 2BR Penthouse with 4 sunny decks
description:
Beautiful, modern 2 bedroom, 2 bath flat with 4 decks, high ceilings and sunny skylights, home automation system, all the appliances you could need in the kitchen and Sonos throughout the house. Upstairs office with a terrific view for working. Near the 10 and 22 MUNI buses.

The space
Incredible views from the four decks of this Potrero Hill loft complement a sunny, modern interior. This amazing loft is right in the heart of Potrero Hill for great food, easy parking & access, sunny weather, and convenient central SF location. Plants abound inside and out, and complement the clean, fresh look and feel of this California flat. Excellent views of downtown and Twin Peaks from the decks.

Inside, enjoy 2 full bedrooms and baths (including a California King size Tempurpedic mattress in master bedroom and a brand new Queen size memory foam mattress in the second bedroom), an open layout, and modern, loft-style living with 25 foot ceilings. A fantastic kitchen
neighborhood_overview: Potrero Hill is known for its sunny weather, great views of the city, easy access to both 101 and 280 (only 15 minutes from SFO), and close proximity to the Mission, Dogpatch and SoMa. Lots of great restaurants, bars and live music venues just 2 blocks from our house including Mexican, Vietnamese, Peruvian, Italian, French, Pizza, Sushi and brunch.
host_about: Hi there, we are Reid and Tara, avid travellers and friendly folks. Reid has been in SF since 1999 and we've owned our beautiful home together since 2010. We now split our time, when Tara isn't teaching at SF State University, between SF and a cabin lodging business outside of Yosemite, in the beautiful Sierra foothills. We love sharing our home and our neighborhood (Potrero Hill, the best and sunniest neighborhood in SF, we think!) with fellow travelers from near and far.

name: Spacious Gem to Entertain or Relax
description:
Our home is a perfect spot for a family or group of friends visiting SF: equipped with an open-layout, modern kitchen/dining room; walking distance to a supermarket, drugstore, and Starbucks; and ample parking or easy access to public transportation.

The space
Our home is an immaculate Spanish style home with 1800 sq ft of finished space in charming Old Miraloma. Our 2-level corner property features lots of natural light, vaulted ceilings, parquet floors, recessed lighting, and views of Mt. Davidson. The eat-in Chef's kitchen includes stainless steel appliances, custom cabinets, slate tile floor, and a granite island and breakfast bar with large skylight. The dining area and living room with fireplace and flatscreen are also on the main level, along with a remodeled tile-and-marble bathroom with Jacuzzi and glass shower stall. Two bedrooms are on this same level, with one set up as a proper guestroom with Queen, and the other as a nursery (with crib). This bedro
neighborhood_overview: Miraloma Park is a residential neighborhood that has old San Francisco charm. (Our home was built in 1937, for example.) In our central location, you are close to the action but not in the action. Our home is a short bus ride or cab ride away from fun neighborhoods like the Castro and the Mission so you can go out to dinner and drinks but then return to a quiet refuge after a day of activities. It's close to public transportation which makes reaching downtown simple and quick. There is a shopping center with a grocery store, a sandwich shop, a burger joint, a pizza place, a drug store, and a Starbucks right behind our house. And if you want to experience nature there are many trails at Mt. Davidson and in Glen Canyon Park, both right in our 'hood, that are perfect for that morning jog or urban hike!
host_about:
I am a proud resident of the vibrant City by the Bay!  After growing up on the East Coast, I moved to SF in my early 20's, and here I am, 7 years later and still loving every moment here.  My husband Chris and I are now in our 30's, and as much as we enjoy our time in San Francisco, we spend many weekends visiting friends & family, skiing in Tahoe and traveling to new places.  We bought a beautiful home last year and want to join AirBnB so others can take advantage of our great place while we're away.

More about us...during the week, Chris is a high school teacher and I work at a hedge fund.  Our weekends in town often involve dance music, watching sporting events, and  doing activities like tennis and cycling to stay healthy together.  We love the big, fun network of energetic SF friends that always keeps us on our toes.  We are excited about the opportunity to meet new folks through airbnb and to help visitors have the best time ever while in SF.

name: Historic SF Residence on a park
description:
Central location, well maintained Victorian, great for families. We're right on a park so it's green and quiet, but in the city.

The space
Central location, well maintained Victorian, great for families. We're right on a park so it's green and quiet, but in the city.

Enjoy a historic, 1750 sq. ft. Victorian flat in the heart of San Francisco, right on Duboce Park and close to a MUNI subway station. It is a beautiful 3 bedroom / 2 bath condo. There are 2 large bedrooms with queen beds. 1 large kids bedroom with a twin bed; And a bonus: A 2nd twin bed is in a little 'secret kids room' with doors -- that is a mini 4th room. So 4 rooms in total -- is you count the bonus room off of the large kids bedroom.

We've recently renovated our home with 2 full bathrooms and new kitchen appliances. And though we have kids, we do a great job of keeping the kid stuff out of site in the living areas.

We're the last in a row of Victor

description:
Entire single family home in great relationship to large private garden, decks with views and three stories in transformed Victorian. Artist and designer/owners crafted this beautiful spacious haven close to great local restaurants, shops, parks, cafes and a gym. Open plan living space filled with folk and contemporary art. 3 bedrooms w/ queen beds and 2.5 baths. Warm and personal, a one of a kind getaway, fully renovated with updated kitchen and generous gathering spaces.

The space
This sunny 3 bedroom, 2 1/2 bath house with with open plan updated kitchen, dining and living room with contemporary and folk art is on three floors. Artist/designer renovation. In the heart of Bernal Heights, we are just blocks from the main artery with San Francisco's best: bakeries, butcher, grocer, extra special restaurants, gym, bars, shops, public library and the panoramic view over the Bay Area- all just a few blocks away on top of Bernal Hill. An additional library roo
neighborhood_overview: We have lived in and loved this neighborhood and house for over 30 years. The natural setting of the hill with panorama views to the bay and the Golden Gate are unbeatable. For so long,  a hidden treasure now discovered but with that came other amenities like amazing local, artisanal food, great restaurants and cafes, bakeries, gym, library, good bars and music adjacent to The Mission district.  In a village like environment full of gardens and secret spots, we have some of the warmest, sunniest weather in SF. Wonderful Alemany Farmer's Market on Saturday and Flea Market on Sunday.

name: Unwind with a BBQ at a Cozy, Stylish Mission Home
description:
Come to San Francisco and stay in an architect-designed, unique, modern, luxury, two bedroom apartment. Perfect for one guest, two guests, two couples, as well as a family with one or two children. The Mission is where you want to be, and this place puts you in the absolute heart of it all, while being quiet and safe.

Each bedroom has French doors that open onto the private patio as well as transom windows that flood the apartment with light. A third French door from the living room completes the open aesthetic. Queen-sized beds with fresh, high-quality linens can be found on both beds, along with a large closet with hangers for your suits and dresses, and luggage racks for your suitcases.

The living room has a huge Room & Board couch (perfect for lounging and snuggling), a designer side chair, and mid-century modern furniture classic, the Carter Brothers chair. For entertainment, you'll have a 46" TV and Roku box where you can watch Netflix, HuluPlus, etc. (simpl
neighborhood_overview: This apartment in the Mission is close to it all while remaining quiet and safe. Try world-class pastries and bread or the best ice cream in town at Tartine Bakery. Indulge in the best thin-crust pizza this side of Naples at Delfina Pizzeria.
host_about: I love the urban environment of San Francisco where I live, and I enjoy exploring other cities and the countryside around the world, especially living where the locals live, so I really like Airbnb.

name: The top of Liberty Hill, near BART
description:
A spacious flat with nice views -from a family who lives in it most of the time -in a quiet street in one of SF's best neighborhoods. 4 bedrooms, 2 baths, sleep 10, walking distance to public transport and to the restaurants of the Mission. The place has plenty of charm and quirks, to experience the city like a true San Franciscan.

The space
Full flat: a large unit at the top of Liberty Hill, near the Valencia corridor and with easy access to BART, MUNI, public transportation and freeways.

The 4 rooms are independent. One holds a king size bed, two have a queen size bed and the last one has a queen size and also a set of bunk beds. There is a large dining table and even a grand piano. But keep your inner Beethoven in check, it's a middle floor with neighbors above and below.

I live in this flat year round, and I host occasionally on Airbnb when I'm not around***. While you'll have the place to yourself, you won't be in a sterile hotel room

name: Home in the Castro
description:
The Castro is one of San Francisco's historic neighborhoods. Original Victorian homes populate tree lined streets and cafes, restaurants, shops, and nightclubs are all a stone's throw away.

The space
Old world charm meets modern comfort at this home in the heart of the Castro, one of San Francisco's most vibrant neighborhoods.

This is a two-story home. Upstairs, you'll find three private bedrooms to retreat to at the end of a full day. The master bedroom features a king sized bed and city views. The second bedroom is equipped with a queen sized bed and opens to a private balcony overlooking the backyard garden. The third bedroom has a full sized bed.

We have locked a few cabinets and the garage for our private belongings.

There is an in-law style bedroom below the main house. Please do not disturb the guests in the private room below the main house. They have their own private street entrance.

name: Stylish Edwardian Family Home
description:
Our lovely 2000 sq foot 2BD home is located in the upscale Lake St district. Our neighborhood is quiet and safe. Parking is easy -- no permits needed. Several bus lines within a short walk. You will fall in love with our comfortable home & garden

The space
Our lovely home is comfortable and peaceful. Spend some time relaxing in our large garden. Enjoy the privacy with birds singing and sun shining . Have a picnic lunch.

Have fun preparing a meal in our updated kitchen featuring granite countertops, commercial stove, and stainless appliances, and then enjoy the fruits of your labor in our large dining room with soft music in the background.

Enjoy your morning coffee (or Nespresso) in our breakfast nook overlooking the garden.

host_about:
My husband and I have been together for 11 years and have traveled to the corners of the country and beyond. Ryan spent some time growing up in the Bay Area and we returned to SF in 2013.

Being avid travelers who frequently used hotels and tried a different homesharing site, those experiences did not compare to the TLC we received when staying with family and friends. We realized that adding little touches like family artwork, a welcome kit with snacks, wine, fresh flowers from our yard (when in season) and a stockpile of toiletries in case anything didn't make its way into your suitcase, makes an ordinary place to lay your head a welcoming retreat.

We are both college-educated professionals. We enjoy finding local restaurants, making fun meals at home, exploring our city, and working in the yard.

As a same-sex couple, we understand the need for inclusive accommodations when we travel. We promote an inclusive environment for guests regardless of race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability, or age. 

When we're traveling, Ryan is usually looking for great running routes and I'm looking for great golf courses to play. Together, we seek out delicious local restaurants, warm beaches, and activities that give us a greater sense of local culture.

Thanks for checking out our profile and we look forward to welcoming you to San Francisco or seeing you wherever our travels take us!

host_about:
'Not all who wander are lost.' I love this quote. 
I am that wanderer, incredibly lucky to be infected with the passion and audacity to travel often and solo. 
I was born and raised in San Francisco. I am a native. I love my city. IÃ¢â¬â¢ve watched it evolve. But I have also left it many times in my youth. IÃ¢â¬â¢ve left it to study abroad in France. Best decision of my college life! I backpacked solo around western Europe. 
IÃ¢â¬â¢ve left SF when I was in the military and stationed around our country. IÃ¢â¬â¢ve also driven as far north as Niagara Falls.
Career wise, IÃ¢â¬â¢ve spent over a decade in property management and rentals. I'm also a realtor. As a hobby, I write as often as possible, a pen and notebook on me at all times.
I am cursed with this blessing of being unceasingly interested in people. I love meeting people. I love hearing stories. And I love writing them. 
As I review my lifeÃ¢â¬â¢s experiences, IÃ¢â¬â¢ve come upon one very simple realization, that proclaimed secret of success. It is merely this: Ã¢â¬ËSay what you will do and do what you will say.Ã¢â¬â¢
The prolific Seth Godin, talented blogger said creativity isnÃ¢â¬â¢t the most important part. What counts is being able to ship! Ship on time. And ship again. And again. And again.

Chestnut Street brims with inviting stores, restaurants and watering holes.

host_about:
We have been providing vacation rental apartments for over 10 years across the East Coast. We are known for our distinctively furnished apartments in popular locations, and for our attentive service. YouÃ¢â¬â¢ll find that our rates are quite reasonable. If you're looking for a safe, comfortable place with fabulous amenities and Wi-Fi (we know you need the Wi-Fi!) in the Boston MA area, Washington DC, Miami FL or very close to NYC in Jersey City or Hoboken, we'd love to host you. Many of the buildings where our apartments are located feature amenities such as beautiful lobbies, 24 hour front desk staff, fitness centers, business centers, recreation rooms, indoor or outdoor pools and whirlpools. If you are traveling with children, some buildings offer playgrounds (many buildings are near public playgrounds as well) or indoor playrooms. Depending on the location, you can stay for just a few days, a week, a month or more. 

We offer an assortment of short-term apartments in sizes ranging from a studio to three bedrooms that are fully furnished with all the comforts of home. Our local staff meticulously prepares your apartment before your arrival, and we offer 24 hour assistance for any emergencies after business hours. When you arrive at your apartment, the beds will be made, towels and bath amenities will be stocked in the bathrooms, and the coffee maker will be set up in the kitchen with some sample coffees, sweetener and creamer (teabags too if that is your preference) to start your morning off properly. If youÃ¢â¬â¢d like to cook a meal, the kitchen is stocked with dishes, cutlery, glassware and pots and pans. The living room is set up with a TV and cable channels, and the Wi-Fi router password and instructions will be prominently displayed so you can get connected quickly. You can also make local and toll-free phone calls at no charge. 

Please contact us to confirm the exact availability of the apartment you are interested in. WeÃ¢â¬â¢d love to host you (and your family) for your vacation or business trip.

name: The Skybox - Buena Vista
description:
Superior top-floor of victorian Buena Vista Park location with sweeping views, must see to believe! Recently renovated, chef's kitchen, hardwood floors, great vibes throughout. Street parking is a snap, adventuring on foot is easy for neighborhood tennis courts, Goat Rocks, Twin Peaks, Clarendon Forest, great restaurants and shops in Haight Ashbury, Castro and beyond. In other words, sublime lodging. We are excited to share this great city with you!

The space
The Skybox is the top unit of a classic Victorian duplex built in 1905 (pre-earthquake). The building adjacent to the north was built in 1961, and was originally a stable or garage for the two Victorians on either side of it. Pretty cool neighborhood.

Guest access
The Skybox is its own universe: enter the key code, climb the stairs, and the entire flat is yours to enjoy. Please do not try to access the attic.

host_about:
Hi! I'm Lawrence, a native of San Francisco, born and raised in the Richmond district. I have deep roots in this city. My father was born here and my mother immigrated here at a very young age. My entire extended family have all stayed local to San Francisco. This city is more than just a magical place, it's who I am. 

As a host: I want everyone to feel like my home is theirs. This is my sanctuary, where I unwind after a long day or spend quality time with family and friends. I hope you love this neighborhood and all that it has to offer as much as I do, from cute mom-and-pop shops to delicious restaurants. I want to make your stay enjoyable, comfortable, and relaxing. Traveling should be fun and easy. Your accommodations should be too!

As a guest, I love exploring new countries and cities. Hotels are nice but staying in local homes is a great way to experience true local living. I enjoy an awesome food scene, stunning architecture, rich colors and textures, and most of all, warm and inviting people. 

I enjoy cooking and eating, working out, yoga, running, tennis, real estate, interior design, and of course, traveling!

name: Spacious Victorian w/Hot Tub and Zen Garden
description:
Welcome to Chateau Clement, your peaceful oasis in SF's Richmond district. Featuring endless Victorian charm, our spacious, bright & airy home offers indoor/outdoor living at its finest. With an oversized living room, comfy bedrooms, a lush zen garden w/jetted hot tub, our home offers a serenity that's hard to find in the middle of the city. Whimsical elements mix with modern amenities, offering the ultimate in comfort & relaxation. Feel like a local while enjoying the best that SF has to offer!

The space
Our classic Victorian home is quintessential San Francisco. The house is located on famous Clement Street, which is known for some of the best cuisine in the entire city. It is also in close proximity to world-class attractions such as Golden Gate Park, Golden Gate Bridge, Fisherman's Wharf and Union Square.

name: Beautiful 2 bedroom downtown
description:
Modern Single family house 2-bedroom & 1 bathroom conveniently located near Financial District, Chinatown, Union Square and public transportation.

One of the original seven hills of San Francisco, Nob Hill is rated 99 out of 100 on a walk ability scale. Centrally located, the home is situated 2 blocks from Grace Cathedral and Huntington Park. With Powell Street BART station only a short walk through Lower Nob Hill and Union Square and several MUNI connections, all of San Francisco at your feet

name: Bernal Heights Home
description:
Bask in the warm Bernal Heights sun in this modern light filled home on two levels boasting a wraparound deck, lush backyard and dramatic 180 views.

The space
The house has 2 full bedrooms and bathrooms. One bedroom has a king size bed with en-suite bathroom and direct access to a private backyard. The second bedroom has a bunk bed with two twin beds. The upstairs has a queen size pullout couch with a small office attached. Please note that there is a small occupied unit downstairs.

Other things to note
Welcome to our modern home in the trendy Bernal Heights neighborhood. You will enjoy a short 2 block walk to our special main street with coffee shops, restaurants, bars, and a small grocery store. Plus 3 parks (Holly Park, St Marys and Bernal Hill). Our home has lots of natural light, and a large private garden and wraparound roof deck. Easy drive to downtown, coastal beaches, hiking trails, and the airport. The street is very quiet with l
neighborhood_overview: Bernal is one of the cutest and most walkable neighborhoods in San Francisco. It is like its own little village with lots of parks, playgrounds and green space. Our place is a 5 minute walk to Cortland with its great restaurants, grocery shops, cafes, and bars.
